---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

// Public data-deletion reference. Underdial has no accounts, all collection
// data is stored on-device, so deletion is a local action, documented here for
// transparency and App Store review.
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Delete Your Data"
  description="How to delete your Underdial data. There is no account, your collection lives on your device, so deletion is a local action."
  path="/delete-account"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'Delete Your Data', url: `${SITE.url}/delete-account` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
  <h1>Delete Your Data</h1>
  <p class="effective">Underdial has no account. Your collection lives on your device, so you control deletion entirely.</p>

  <h2>Option 1: Reset From Inside the App (recommended)</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Open Underdial on your iPhone.</li>
    <li>Tap the <strong>Settings</strong> tab.</li>
    <li>Scroll to the bottom and tap <strong>Reset Data</strong>.</li>
    <li>Confirm by tapping <strong>Reset</strong>.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Your box, wrist settings, and check history are removed immediately.</p>

  <h2>Option 2: Delete the App</h2>
  <p>
    Because nothing is stored on our servers, deleting Underdial from your iPhone
    removes all of its local data along with it. There is no separate server-side
    record to request the deletion of.
  </p>

  <h2>What gets deleted</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Your box (every watch you added).</li>
    <li>Your wrist size and fit preferences.</li>
    <li>Your check history and any saved verdicts.</li>
    <li>Your rotation tracking and Box Audit data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What is retained</h2>
  <p>For legal and billing purposes the following may persist, none of it tied to your identity:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Anonymized purchase records for Underdial Plus (held by Apple).</li>
    <li>Anonymized aggregate analytics that cannot be traced back to you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    Deleting the app or resetting your data does <strong>not</strong> automatically
    cancel an active App Store subscription. You must cancel separately in
    <strong>Settings &rarr; Apple ID &rarr; Subscriptions</strong> on your iPhone,
    or it will continue to renew.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions?</h2>
  <p>
    Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
